               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary>This manuscript is part of an assortment of three fragments found with Sanscrit 1347. This fragment contains a <title xml:lang="sa">Bhuvaneśvarīkavaca</title>, a hymn for protection addressed to the goddess <term xml:lang="sa">Bhuvaneśvarī</term>.  The small size of the manuscript suggests that it may have been used as an amulet or charm.</summary>
                  
